Nikhil Bharadwaj Reddy Sagili
Chicago, IL,
Professional Summary: 
Mission-driven GenAI and AI Automation Engineer with 6+ years of experience in AWS-based machine learning, data engineering, and AI pipeline development. Extensive work with LLMs, including LLaMA and internal GPT models, leveraging Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) techniques to structure large-scale documentation and internal knowledge systems. Certified in AWS, with hands-on experience using Bedrock, SageMaker, and Lambda to build and deploy scalable, cloud-based AI solutions. Skilled in constructing ETL pipelines and architecting end-to-end solutions that process sensitive customer and medical data. Proficient in developing GenAI systems using LangChain, LangGraph, Python, and REST APIs, with seamless integration into enterprise tools such as Salesforce, HubSpot, and Slack. Strong track record of reducing manual processes by over 85% and delivering impactful automation across business operations.
Skills: 
Languages & Technologies: Python, Java, SQL, Bash, JavaScript, Linux, HTML/CSS 
Cloud & Data Engineering: AWS (Glue, Lambda, S3, CloudWatch, SQS, SNS, EKS, EC2,S3….), Airflow, dbt, Terraform, GKE 
Databases: PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, DynamoDB, Snowflake, Redshift 
Big Data & Streaming: Apache Kafka, Apache Spark, Hadoop, EMR 
Version Control & CI/CD: Git, GitHub, Jenkins, CI/CD Pipelines 
Containerization & IaC: Docker, Kubernetes, Cloud Composer, dbt, Terraform 
AI & LLMs: OpenAI GPT-4, Llama,LangChain, Retrieval-Augmented Generation, vector DB (Pinecone) 
Automation & Integration: Python, Zapier, Make.com, REST APIs, Apache Airflow,n8n 
Tooling & Dashboards: Retool, Streamlit, Slack Apps, GitHub Actions, Jenkins 
GenAI Frameworks & Tools: LangChain, LangGraph, LlamaIndex, FAISS, Pinecone, sentence-BERT, OpenAI GPT-4, Claude, Azure OpenAI, Azure Cognitive Search 
GenAI Architectures: Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), Model Context Protocol (MCP), prompt scaffolding, tool calling

Health First 							       November 2022 – May 2025
Data & AI Engineer

Developed and deployed a secure, production-grade Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system leveraging LLMs and AWS Bedrock, enabling intelligent semantic querying across internal documentation and knowledge bases. 
Fine-tuned LLaMA and GPT models on domain-specific corpora to enhance contextual relevance and accuracy of generated outputs in the RAG pipeline. 
Engineered a Graph-RAG framework, combining vector stores (using FAISS) with graph databases (Neo4j) to represent and retrieve complex entity relationships and temporal dependencies from unstructured and semi-structured sources. 
Built scalable RAG pipelines in AWS SageMaker for model training and inference, and later transitioned to MLflow for streamlined model tracking, versioning, and CI/CD integration. 
Integrated Azure Cognitive Search and Azure OpenAI to power hybrid cognitive pipelines. 
Developed automated evaluation pipelines leveraging OpenAI Evals, LangSmith, and custom metric frameworks (e.g., answer faithfulness, latency, tool invocation accuracy, token efficiency) to continuously benchmark and improve agent reliability, response quality, and production readiness.
Applied Model Context Protocol (MCP) principles by exposing prompt templates, API tools, and resources for plug-and-play use by LLM agents. 
Created a systematic prompt-engineering framework—including reusable templates, dynamic parameter tuning, and automated A/B evaluation—that consistently boosted LLM answer precision across internal RAG, chatbot, and analytics  
Designed and deployed internal APIs providing users secure access and the flexibility to select various Large Language Models (LLMs) (OpenAI GPT-4, Gemini, Claude, Llama) tailored to specific business needs. 
 Designed and deployed autonomous LLM agents using LangChain’s ReAct and OpenAI Functions paradigms, enabling dynamic decision-making and multi-step reasoning through tool-chaining, contextual memory, and structured output parsing—driving intelligent task orchestration across diverse enterprise workflows.
Developed real-time data processing pipelines utilizing AWS Lambda, API Gateway, Apache Kafka, Python, integrating data between MongoDB and PostgreSQL, and orchestrating event-driven workflows with SQS and SNS for reliable notifications and messaging. 
Architected robust batch data ETL pipelines using AWS Glue and PySpark to process large-scale datasets from MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Apache Kafka, storing optimized analytical outputs in S3 and managing complex data transformations with schema evolution and data validation techniques. 
Implemented end-to-end CI/CD automation leveraging CloudFormation, Jenkins, Docker, and Kubernetes, ensuring rapid deployment, infrastructure scalability, and robust container orchestration for data-intensive AI

from MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Apache Kafka, storing optimized analytical outputs in S3 and managing complex data transformations with schema evolution and data validation techniques. 
Implemented end-to-end CI/CD automation leveraging CloudFormation, Jenkins, Docker, and Kubernetes, ensuring rapid deployment, infrastructure scalability, and robust container orchestration for data-intensive AI applications. 
Designed interactive and insightful analytics dashboards using Tableau and Looker, enabling real-time visualization and monitoring of generated insights, significantly improving strategic decision-making capabilities for stakeholders. 
Exafluence 	June 2019 - August 2022 
Machine Learning Engineer
Developed and deployed internal recommendation models using collaborative filtering and content-based approaches, exposing robust APIs integrated seamlessly into production financial products, significantly enhancing user engagement and product personalization. 
Pioneered hybrid reinforcement-learning–guided diffusion models to generate high-fidelity synthetic market scenarios for stress-testing and data augmentation, boosting forecasting pipeline robustness and cutting overfitting error rates 
Engineered financial forecasting models using time-series analysis and regression techniques to predict market movements and asset valuation trends, supporting high-stakes investment decisions and aligning methodologies closely with leading financial institutions. 
Built, deployed, and maintained over 100 secure, RESTful APIs in Python and Flask, utilized internally across trading, compliance, and risk management teams, improving system interoperability and data-driven decision-making efficiency.

Created an internal Machine Learning Model Repository(has models and transformers) with model versioning, metadata tracking, and automated model validation, improving transparency, reproducibility, and streamlined access to production-grade ML models across business units. 
Designed and implemented an advanced BERT-based NLP chatbot (Hugging Face) capable of interpreting complex financial documents and responding accurately to user queries, automating internal knowledge sharing and significantly reducing manual information retrieval time. 
MLGround 							          October 2018 – May 2019 
Machine Learning Engineer Intern
Leveraged Python, TensorFlow, and Keras to prototype and train a convolutional neural-network pipeline that used OpenCV preprocessing and a one-class SVM post-filter, boosting breast-cancer slide-image detection accuracy from 91 % to 96 %. 
Packaged the model with BentoML for low-latency REST inference; tracked versions, metrics, and artifacts in MLflow, laying the groundwork for reproducible, auditable deployments. 
Automated end-to-end MLOps by integrating Git-based triggers with containerized builds (Docker) and Kubernetes staging/production clusters, enabling rollbacks and blue-green releases in under 10 minutes. 
Built an automated data-augmentation framework in Python using OpenCV and imgaug to synthesize histopathology images, tripling the training set size and improving model F1-score by 7 %. 
Orchestrated a continuous training pipeline that scheduled TensorFlow/Keras jobs via Airflow, logged experiments to MLflow, containerized releases with Docker, and served them through BentoML, halving model iteration time.

Projects:

AI-Powered Document Intelligence System 
Built a RAG-based document processing system using LangChain, OpenAI APIs, and Pinecone vector database that automatically extracted key information from unstructured documents with 90% accuracy 
Integrated the solution with existing data pipelines in Snowflake and AWS RDS, enabling semantic search capabilities that reduced information retrieval time by 85% 
Review Management Automation 
Designed a review ingestion pipeline using Zapier and AWS Lambda that captures customer feedback from multiple platforms in real time. Once captured stores the data in Mongodb 
Applied GPT-driven sentiment analysis and auto-response generation, sending personalized replies via SMTP,  The emails are operated through CronJob at a particular time daily and  cutting manual reply workload by 90% while boosting repeat visits by 25%. 
AI Personalized Storybook Generator for Children 
Developed a serverless workflow on AWS Lambda, S3, and DynamoDB, S3 that takes a child’s photo and metadata, then invokes GPT-4o and a custom illustration service to produce a personalized, illustrated storybook in under two minutes. 
Automated file assembly and delivery using Python and AWS Step Functions, So A personalized story book for a kid is generated. 
AI Waiter 
Built a Telegram/ Slack/ web -integrable chatbot using Python, LangChain Agents,  Rasa ,RAG, Pinecone and OpenAI that answers menu queries, logs diner preferences, and suggests dishes or Personalized Discount coupons based on order history. 
Connected via Zapier to the POS and CRM systems, auto-updating customer profiles and driving a uplift in add-on sales by delivering real-time, context-aware recommendations. 
AI Phone Call Assistant 
Implemented a Twilio + AWS Transcribe + OpenAI + ElevenLabs pipeline that answers inbound calls, handles menu questions, captures orders, and emails confirmations without human operators. 
Deployed automated caller-ID lookup and personalized greeting logic with DynamoDB and AWS Lambda, handling calls end-to-end and doubling peak-hour order throughput. 
Personal Daily Assistant 
Created a daily briefing bot using Python, Google Workspace APIs, and OpenAI that reads yesterday’s emails and calendar events, then sends a concise agenda summary to Slack or Telegram. 
Scheduled with AWS EventBridge and automated via a Zapier webhook, saving executives 15 minutes of morning email triage and ensuring no task or meeting is overlooked.
